cs.HC, cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.GR 

The paper focuses on the design of a serious game for security education, which involves user interaction and motivation. Therefore, the most likely category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), followed by Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the use of mobile devices and social elements, which could fall under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Graphics (cs.GR) respectively.
